add_to_list¶

orbitpy.util.add_to_list(existing_list, inp_list)[source]¶

Add input list to an existing list. The existing “list” and input “list” are checked to see if they are list instances, and if not configured to be a lists. The existing list is extended with the input list.

Parameters

  • existing_list (list) – Existing list, which needs to be extended. Can be made of heterogenous objects.

  • inp_list (list) – Input list. Can be made of heterogenous objects.

Returns

Extended list.

Return type

list
